				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Vinyl chloride is a colorless gas with a sweet odor at high concentrations. It is used in the production of polyvinyl chloride (PVC), a material used to manufacture a variety of plastic products. Vinyl chloride monomer (VCM) is an IARC group 1 carcinogen known to cause hepatic angiosarcoma (HAS) in highly exposed industrial workers. VCM is a component in the production of PVC resins. It is a halogenated hydrocarbon with acute toxic effects, as well as chronic carcinogenic effects.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯乙烯是一种无色气体，浓度高时有甜味。它用于生产聚氯乙烯（PVC），这是一种用于制造各种塑料产品的材料。氯乙烯单体（VCM）是国际癌症研究机构（IARC）的 1 类致癌物质，已知会导致高度接触该物质的产业工人患上肝血管肉瘤（HAS）。氯乙烯单体是生产聚氯乙烯树脂的一种成分。它是一种卤代烃，具有急性毒性和慢性致癌作用。</common:generalComment>
